reviews.text: Had Esquite and Fresas Con Crema, was extremely delicious! And was offered samples of the juices that are served on menu as well was extremely satisfied with the food as well as the service ! Great place to come and try out! Will definitely be back for the horchata drink and friendly staff ! Great job!! üëèüèΩ
Excellent place, the atmosphere is amazing. The staff was super helpful and attentive. Great options definitely recommend.

First time here at this location and let me tell you. The options are endless and the prices are not outrageous. I didn‚Äôt really know what to order but I was helped by Sara and let me tell you this woman knows her stuff!!! She recommended about half the menu but in the end I went with the Mangoneada and let me tell you I wasn‚Äôt disappointed! It was a hot day and this had a mix of sweet,fresh, and spicy added all in one! Definitely a 10 out of 10! I will be coming here more often and thanks to Sara for the great customer service she provided. I will definitely recommend this place to all my friends hands down. Great job guys.

Update: the owner, Noe, let us come again their year on our field trip. Again, the ice cream was sooooo good. The kids were happy and the employees were so kind to us! Thank you!

We took our special needs class on a field trip here! The kids loved it! The ice cream was so good! All the kids and teachers loved it! The employees were so kind to our kids and the owner Noe was so great to let us come!

I have been visiting Fruteria for a year now, they are very kind and accommodating to my marketing needs, specially when I have a large order. I have tried almost all items on the menu and have received very satisfactory reviews from my marketing visits. I let them know the two locations I go to most and hand them the info. Thank you for the delicious treats that take me back to my childhood. Absolutely LOVE FRUTERIA!

detailedReviews.text: Most of the staff is great. There is just this one worker who is super rude. I am allergic to pineapple, so I order my snacks differently than how they make it. I opened my order and it had pineapple. I went inside so they could fix it. The girl who was there said it wasn't her fault that I never said no pineapple. Again, I am allergic. She said I had to pay for another one since it was my fault I ordered it wrong. On my second order, she put gummy worms on my food. I never asked for gummy worms. I was so confused about why she said I ordered it wrong when she wrote  it down. I love this place, and most of the workers. I was shocked when she said it was my fault, lol. I'll probably still go back but won't let them bully me into buying another one when it was their mistake.

detailedReviews.author: Dayana Aristondo
detailedReviews.text: I came to this place a couple of days ago for the first time with some friends. I ordered the mangoneada to give it a try. My resistance to spicy flavors is pretty bad so I asked to the girl who took my order if she could remove the spicy ingredients and replace them with something non-spicy, she made a wonderful choice of replacements for my order which I loved 100%. The customer service attention was so good. In this case, Angie surprised me with her positive, welcoming, and warming attitude so I can enjoy my experience at Fruiteria better. I'll for sure go back again! The options for ice cream or a refreshing treat are so good and delicious!
